            <title>[HBASE-2324] Refactoring of TableRecordReader (mapred / mapreduce) for reuse outside the scope of InputSplit / RecordReader </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2324</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the storing of tf-idf in hbase ( lucene-hbase project) we need to scan the keys across the table and retrieve columnar values.  Quite an amount of logic can be reused from TableRecordReader for the purpose. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Refactored TableRecordReader ( from being a protected inner class to a public class outside )&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Created an impl class , that does the actual work, without the dependency on hadop.mapreduce.* packages ( RecordReader) while retaining the implementation that can be reused across libraries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Do the same thing for .mapred. and .mapreduce. packages. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know the thoughts on the same. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
